WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:02.360
Previously on <i>Bones...</i>

00:02.362 --> 00:03.695
<i>There's a hacker named</i>

00:03.730 --> 00:05.498
Christopher Pelant.
Where are you?

00:05.532 --> 00:07.400
Pretty much anywhere
I want to be.

00:07.434 --> 00:09.101
This guy's killed how many people?
Eight.

00:09.136 --> 00:10.636
<i>This guy is worse than anyone</i>

00:10.671 --> 00:12.371
<i>you and I</i>
<i>have ever come across.</i>

00:12.406 --> 00:14.140
And he told you that if you
married Temperance, that

00:14.174 --> 00:16.943
<i>he would choose five random</i>
<i>human beings and kill them?</i>

00:16.977 --> 00:19.111
<i>Not only if I married</i>
<i>Bones but if I told her</i>

00:19.146 --> 00:21.013
why we couldn't get married.

00:22.850 --> 00:24.584
What kind of
flower is that?

00:24.618 --> 00:25.885
It's a marigold.

00:25.919 --> 00:27.553
What's that mean?
Pain and grief.

00:27.588 --> 00:28.721
Christopher Pelant,

00:28.755 --> 00:30.056
<i>you are under arrest.</i>

00:30.090 --> 00:31.924
We have nothing on him.
So Pelant wins?

00:31.959 --> 00:33.559
<i>Yes, today</i>

00:33.594 --> 00:34.961
Pelant wins.

00:35.529 --> 00:36.929
Down!

00:38.131 --> 00:39.732
<i>Been looking for this guy</i>

00:39.766 --> 00:41.367
for three months,
and I got nothing.

00:41.401 --> 00:42.501
<i>It's a complete dead end.</i>

00:42.536 --> 00:44.036
Pelant's laughing
at us right now.

00:44.071 --> 00:45.805
The key will be to tie Pelant
to the murders specifically.

00:46.773 --> 00:48.274
<i>Pelant is still out there.</i>

00:48.308 --> 00:51.077
<i>We're still waiting for him</i>
<i>to make the next move.</i>

00:56.850 --> 00:58.818
Hey, I-I love
the closeness, sweetie,

00:58.852 --> 01:00.653
but isn't there something else
you could be doing?

01:00.687 --> 01:02.255
Just want to make sure
the shield works.

01:02.289 --> 01:04.757
Yeah, well, I've set up
a trident sub's worth

01:04.791 --> 01:06.325
of microwave-emitting
jammers.

01:06.360 --> 01:08.641
There is no way that Pelant
is hacking through this thing.

01:08.662 --> 01:09.695
Hey, Sweets,

01:09.730 --> 01:12.131
what are you doing here?
Thought you were on leave.

01:12.132 --> 01:14.567
Well, this whole idea
started with me.

01:14.601 --> 01:16.469
Pelant thinks he's
smarter than all of us,

01:16.503 --> 01:18.104
which might be true,

01:18.138 --> 01:21.440
but he's not smarter
than all of us put together.

01:21.475 --> 01:22.842
Hey, is this
the guy?

01:22.876 --> 01:25.111
Yes.

01:28.982 --> 01:33.653
Late 30s, excellent dentition,
good tone.

01:33.687 --> 01:35.922
His name was Donald Hestnes.

01:35.956 --> 01:37.423
Yeah, what happened
to him?

01:37.457 --> 01:38.991
Coronary occlusion.

01:39.026 --> 01:40.526
Fortunately
he had willed his body

01:40.560 --> 01:42.361
to the Jeffersonian.

01:42.396 --> 01:44.263
Somehow I don't think this is
quite what he had in mind.

01:44.298 --> 01:45.331
Do you object
to our plan,

01:45.365 --> 01:46.399
Ms. Julian?

01:46.433 --> 01:48.567
Legally it passes muster, as the
deceased donated

01:48.602 --> 01:50.202
his body to science.

01:50.237 --> 01:54.674
That being said, what you're
doing gives me the chills.

01:54.708 --> 01:56.108
The situation necessitates it.

01:56.143 --> 01:57.410
Pelant's fundamental
personality structure is

01:57.444 --> 02:01.047
psychopathic
with extreme narcissism

02:01.081 --> 02:02.214
that demands an audience.
Less shrinky, <i>cher.</i>

02:02.249 --> 02:03.616
He won't be able

02:03.650 --> 02:05.217
to tolerate someone else
stealing his spotlight.

02:05.252 --> 02:06.485
We're going to smoke him out.

02:06.520 --> 02:07.787
I, uh,

02:07.821 --> 02:11.557
conceptualized
a copycat body drop.

02:11.591 --> 02:13.225
Pelant usually goes
for the baroque,

02:13.260 --> 02:15.061
so I modeled it
after a painting

02:15.095 --> 02:16.629
by Salvator Rosa.

02:16.663 --> 02:18.564
The punishment
of Prometheus.

02:18.598 --> 02:21.300
He was bound to a rock
and his liver was torn out

02:21.335 --> 02:23.369
- by a giant eagle.
- That body may not be

02:23.403 --> 02:25.237
sufficiently degraded
for us to get the call.

02:25.272 --> 02:27.974
I already took care
of that.

02:29.242 --> 02:31.243
Aw, Angie,

02:31.278 --> 02:32.645
that is brilliant.

02:32.679 --> 02:34.447
Yeah, I kind of
hate it.

02:34.481 --> 02:36.248
We'd better get
to it.

02:40.554 --> 02:44.657
♪ Name

02:45.759 --> 02:50.196
♪ This night

02:53.400 --> 02:56.369
♪ And hold me here

02:56.403 --> 02:58.404
♪ Till morning

02:58.438 --> 03:02.074
♪ Takes my eyes

03:06.413 --> 03:09.782
♪ Name

03:11.118 --> 03:15.688
♪ This song

03:18.358 --> 03:22.061
♪ And hold my voice

03:22.095 --> 03:27.233
♪ Till silence takes it down

03:31.071 --> 03:35.041
♪ There's a secret here

03:35.075 --> 03:40.212
♪ A grown man could not find

03:44.017 --> 03:48.721
